
In this study, we are presented the clinical and the aetiologic features of 47 patients having hypercalcemia (total serum calcium &gt; or = 2.7 mmol/l). Our results show a positive significantly correlation between the degree of the hypercalcemia and the severity of the clinical symptomatology. As for to the aetiology, the multiple myeloma, the hyperparathyroid and the neoplastic process constituted 78% of the total aetiology.

